UPDATE 10:AM: Zoom is reporting all issues causing outages this moring have been resolved.

8:15AM: Unfortunately, Zoom is reporting that they are having issues that are causing users to be unable to authenticate to the Zoom website and unable to start and join Zoom meetings.

Zoom is aware of the issue and their development team is working on a fix for this issue.

Until Zoom is back online, please log into your student's Google Classroom or SeeSaw where teachers will be posting what the plan is for today. Teachers may be using Google Meet for online instruction today.

As soon as Zoom has resolved this issue, we will let you know. Thank you for your patience and flexibility.

REMINDER: Today is the last day for priority registration for Connections, Dry Creek’s home -based distance learning option for the 2020-21 school year. To register and to learn more about this program please visit www.drycreekschools.us/connections.

FAQ: “What is the biggest difference between Connections and distance learning?”

A: Connections is a year-long distance program blending virtual and independent learning from home. This is a separate program and not tied to a school site. Students will have an online cohort of students in a virtual classroom setting with their own teacher.

Students enrolled in our traditional school program may be subject to pivoting between distance learning and different forms of in-person instruction at their school site based on public health orders throughout the school year.

This year's 8th Grade Promotion Ceremony for Silverado had to be reimagined. In addition to an upcoming virtual ceremony, they decided to celebrate our 8th graders promoting to high school with great fanfare in a "Pump Up Parade." On May 15, hundreds of decorated cars filled with students and their families drove through Silverado with teachers and staff cheering them on, and handed a complementary yard sign congratulating them on their accomplishment. One of the parents was kind enough to create this video documenting the joy, laughter, and happy tears felt during this celebration. #DCJESDPROUD

Apple App Store: https://apps.apple.com/us/app/ca-meals-for-kids/id1327449394

Google Play Store: https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=gov.ca.cde.NSDMobileApp

Microsoft App Store: https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/p/ca-meals-for-kids/9p7t6j276zz9?activetab=pivot:overviewtab
